# Visual Depth, Color Cycling & Polish

## Objective
Implement advanced visual effects including glow effects, color cycling, agent status animations, and enhanced confirm/loading states to complete the arcade character select aesthetic.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Enhance Color Interpolation System

**File: `internal/ui/model_view.go`**

Replace simple interpolateColor with proper RGB blending:

```go
// parseHexColor parses hex color string to RGB
func parseHexColor(c string) (uint8, uint8, uint8, error) {
    // Handle AdaptiveColor - for now, just extract hex
    // AdaptiveColor{Light: "230", Dark: "230"} -> "230"
    // In practice, we'll use direct hex colors

    var r, g, b uint8
    _, err := fmt.Sscanf(c, "#%02x%02x%02x", &r, &g, &b)
    if err != nil {
        // Try without # prefix
        _, err = fmt.Sscanf(c, "%02x%02x%02x", &r, &g, &b)
        if err != nil {
            // Fallback to ANSI color codes - return default
            return 200, 200, 200, err
        }
    }
    return r, g, b, nil
}

// interpolateColor blends between two RGB colors
func interpolateColor(c1, c2 lipgloss.Color, t float64) lipgloss.Color {
    // If both are the same, return one
    if c1 == c2 || t <= 0 {
        return c1
    }
    if t >= 1 {
        return c2
    }

    // Parse colors
    r1, g1, b1, _ := parseHexColor(string(c1))
    r2, g2, b2, _ := parseHexColor(string(c2))

    // Linear interpolation
    r := uint8(float64(r1) + (float64(r2)-float64(r1))*t)
    g := uint8(float64(g1) + (float64(g2)-float64(g1))*t)
    b := uint8(float64(b1) + (float64(b2)-float64(b1))*t)

    // Format back to hex
    return lipgloss.Color(fmt.Sprintf("#%02x%02x%02x", r, g, b))
}
```

